http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.@value: This ontology aims to model the Occupancy Behavior domain according to the obXML schema (https://behavior.lbl.gov/?q=obXML)
The action the occupant performs to satisfy its need.
Class that represent the behaviour of the occupant.
Building where the occupancy behaviors occur.
N-ary class to represent the value and the names of coefficients inside mathematical formulas.
Parameter to represent the indoor daylight.
Circumstances that motivate the occupant behavior.
N-ary class to define the time, day and season when a specific driver occurs.
Class to represent the environmental physical conditions that could be causing the occupant behavior.
Class that represent a physical variable of the environment where the driver occurs. It could represent variables that impact directly on the comfort levels of the occupant.
Class to represent equipments the occupant interact with but do not influence the environment. These systems also contribute in the energy performance analysis.
Parameter to represent the glare inside a space.
Class to represent occupant habits.
Parameter to represent the indoor air quality.
Parameter to represent the amount of illumination inside a space.
The Inaction class represents the decision of an occupant to not act and remain uncomfortable within a space
The Interaction class represents the interaction of the occupant with the systems within the space to recover its comfort.
Class to represent a meeting inside a communal space.
The Movement class is used to represent the occupants movements inside a space.
Parameter to represent the amount of indoor and outdoor noise
Occupant within the building.
N-ary class to represent the minimum and maximm comfort values for an occupant.
Parameter to represent raining outdoors.
Parameter to represent indoor and outdoor relative humidity.
The Report class indicates that an occupant seeks assistance or files a complaint about their personal discomfort, but does not take direct action to satisfy their needs.
Parameter to represent solar irradiance indoors and outdoors.
Class to represent the different spaces the building have and where the occupant behaviors occur.
Parameter to represent indoor and outdoor temperature.
